<section>
<h2>What is this list for?</h2>
<p>Here is a list of classic stories and novels from English
literature that are freely available online in excellent ebook
editions from Project Gutenberg.</p>
<p>Any of these titles might feature in an English teacher‚Äôs
list of recommended reading.</p>
<p>Some of them are included in the GCSE exam syllabus. </p>
<h2>How to use this list</h2>
<p>All of the entries include a link to download a version of
the text encoded using the EPUB file format for ebooks.</p>
<p>On most phones, tablets and computers, downloading an EPUB
file will automatically open in the default Ebook reader on
the device. If this doesn't happen automatically, save the
file in your Downloads folder, and open it using your Ebook
reader app. </p>
<p>Most Apple devices have <a
href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/apple-books/id364709193&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1678812652841747&amp;usg=AOvVaw3Et_T1LKObYHkxdUbx6guk">Apple
Books</a> installed . On Android, many free EPUB Ebook
reader apps are available: one of the best is <a
href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id%3Dcom.faultexception.reader%26hl%3Den_US&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1678812652842268&amp;usg=AOvVaw3zKqzyJ3A2WxXSOmEW3TFj">Lithium</a>.
No one has a Windows phone! ü§£ </p>
<p>In the app, you can change settings to suit your reading
preferences. T<font size="+1">e<font size="+2">xt</font></font>
<font size="+2">si</font><font size="+1">z</font>e and <font
style="background-color: #ddddff">background colour</font>,
for example. </p>
<p>In many ebook reader apps, you can also add highlights and
notes as you read.</p>
<p>Setting the app to display books in a continuous scroll may
be a more natural way to read long texts on a phone than
swiping ‚Äúpages‚Äù. In Lithium you can swipe between chapters,
which makes some books easier to navigate.</p>
<p>Whichever app you use, as you download EPUB titles, you will
gradually grow a library of all the titles that you have read!</p>
</section>


